additional income while still maintaining the freedom to do the things you love most. No one knows better than a retiree how much the world can change in a lifetime. And 4Retirees is the network that helps you keep up with and benefit from those changesall at a pace youre comfortable with.</p>\n												Do I have to be tech-savvy to use 4Retirees?					\n					<p>No. 4Retirees is run for retirees, by retirees. Weve made it easy for you to get started. If you can read and tap on a keyboard, you can participate now and take our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>. And, when youre ready to learn some new technology skills, well be there too. Our aim is to help you to keep pace with this burgeoning economy and part of that is upskilling your technology skills. These improved skills will help you to unlock a future filled with more opportunities for earning income, taking advantage of tools available to you, so that you can live your dream retirement life and keep you better connected to your friends, family, and the rest of the world.</p>\n												Who participates in 4Retirees community?					\n					<p>Anyone who is chasing a dream of freedom is participating in the 4Retirees community. Anyone who is thinking of career change to enable their potential and opportunities can participate in our community and take advantage of whats on offer. If you have an interest in the on-demand economy, we invite you to start your journey here by taking our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check.</strong></a></p>\n												In what ways will I be able to connect with other retirees?  					\n					<p>Our vision is to build a better place for all retirees. Our big goal at first is to bring you all together and to establish the connections. We know that people do business and learn from people they know, like, and trust. So, first things first, well concentrate on providing opportunities to come together so we can all benefit the advantage of the technology and the on-demand economy. We want to create a community of retirees4retirees, eventually we can co-create, build a better place with a better economy where all retirees come to connect, interact, meet, help each other, share their skills, build new ones, volunteer, earn money, and maybe even make some friends! We will provide you soon with opportunities to participate in forums, to connect, chat, share ideas, and ask questions about your fellow community members. You can also connect with the community through most of our social media channels. Make sure to sign up for our eNewsletter so we keep you up to date on our progress as our community grows and becomes an even better place for retirees.</p>\n												How do I manage my subscription preferences?					\n					<p>Once you take our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> or sign up to our eNewsletter, we will create an account for you and send you link to activate via email. You can manage your preferences by accessing right top corner of your account under the button that says &#8216;<a href=\"http://4retirees.com/my-account\" data-wplink-url-error=\"true\">Login</a>&#8216; or <a href=\"http://4retirees.com/my-account\" data-wplink-url-error=\"true\">My account</a>. If you would like to receive our weekly eNewsletter with useful tips and hints, or perhaps you would like to update your interest information so that we can provide you with more comprehensive updates weekly, you can do all of that in through your account preferences.</p>\n												I forgot my password, how do I reset it?					\n					<p>You can manage this under your account &#8211; right top corner &#8211; you can request a password reset, or before you login, reset by clicking on <a href=\"http://4retirees.com/wp-login.php?action=lostpassword\" data-wplink-url-error=\"true\">forgot my password</a>.</p>\n												How do I deactivate my account? 					\n					<p>We would certainly be sorry to see you go, but if you really want to, you can simply unsubscribe from all the communication or you can deactivate your account. You can manage these preferences under the <a href=\"http://4retirees.com/my-account\" data-wplink-url-error=\"true\">My Account</a> tab located in the right top corner, through the button, Deactivate Account.</p>\n		<p>If we didn\'t answer your question or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>		\n			<h2>Learn all about on-demand economy</h2>		\n												What exactly is the on-demand economy?					\n					<p>The on-demand economy is defined as the economic activity created by technology companies that fulfil consumer demand via the immediate provisioning of goods and services. The on-demand economy, also known as a sharing economy or collaborative consumption or the peer economy, is a trending business concept that highlights the ability (and perhaps the preference) of individuals to rent or borrow goods or services and not necessarily buy and own them. Owners rent out something they are not using, such as a car, house, bicycle, or their skills, to someone else using these peer-to-peer services and earning money on demand.</p>\n												Can you give me some examples of businesses in the on-demand economy? 					\n					<p>We have a comprehensive list of over hundreds of on-demand economy businesses right here in Australia. Two that you have most likely heard of are UBER and Airbnb. With UBER, people use their own cars, sign up as drivers, and then transport people or deliver food to other people as part of their peer-to-peer network. You can work on your terms, the hours you want, in the area you want, and still earn money while meeting new people and listening to your favourite radio station. The second example is Airbnb. It is an online marketplace and hospitality service for people to lease or rent short-term lodging including holiday cottages, rooms, apartments, homestays, hostel beds, etc. You can do this all year long if you have a place you never use, for weeks at a time when you are travelling, or just until you find new tenants for your investment property. Its a great contemporary (and cheaper) alternative to hotel accommodation. We can match you with hundreds of these types of businessesthe choice of businesses participating in the on-demand economy is virtually endless and new ones are popping up all the time. Youll be able to find transportation, hobby-related businesses, travel, education, business services, delivery, pet care, and the works!</p>\n												Why is the on-demand economy growing so fast?					\n					<p>The <strong>on-demand economy </strong>is here to stay. And its growth is a given. Whether its renting a room, hiring a driver, renting a parking space, or outsourcing household tasks, the sharing economy is disrupting a range of industries and causing regulators to take note. Technology is making it easier for new marketplaces to be created. Services that used to be high touch, slow to deliver, but yet expensive are now fast and efficient, thanks to technology like smart phones. This creates a better experience for the consumer and also the person providing the service. Australia has a supportive start-up community with new businesses starting up all the time, and we are here to provide you with this comprehensive research in discovering new options for earning an income all the time. Its an incredibly exciting time!</p>\n												How can I start earning money in the on-demand economy? 					\n					<p>The first step is to understand your compatibility with the opportunities available. Take our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> and see if your current circumstances match any of these on-demand businesses and how much you could potentially earn. Once you receive your results, then you decide if it makes sense for you to purchase access to your custom <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List </strong>so that you can then pursue your matching income-generating opportunities.</p>\n												How much I can get paid from the on-demand economy? 					\n					<p>Once you buy your personalised and comprehensive <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List</strong>, you can explore each individual opportunity you matched with, sign up to do it, start working, and start earning from your very first day. In the on-demand economy, you have the potential to earn per hour, per day, per week, or per item or project. Its possible to earn anywhere from $20 per hour to thousands of dollarsor moreper week or per month. Your earning potential depends on your skill set, situation, the opportunities available, and how little or how much youre prepared to do. The choice is yours! And, youre not locked into committing to any time frames. You can dip in or out when it makes sense for you.</p>\n												How do I get paid from these individual on-demand economy businesses?					\n					<p>Each of these businesses have their own individual payment systems and conditions that you should review before signing up. Payment is usually made directly to your bank account or PayPal account. Fast payment is one of the benefits of the on-demand economy. After you have provided a service via one of the on-demand economy businesses, some payments are received within 1-3 business days, others or on a designated day each week or month. We definitely recommend that you to check this with each business before you start. And, we recommend speaking with your accountant or tax/financial adviser about your individual circumstances.</p>\n												Is the on-demand economy legal?					\n					<p>The on-demand economy and participation in it is most definitely legal and it is even supported by Australian Government. You, as a participant in it, are fully supported by Australian Consumer Law while using the on-demand sharing economy. To find out more, <a href=\"http://consumerlaw.gov.au/business-and-the-acl/sharing-economy-platforms/\">CLICK HERE</a>.</p>\n												Do I pay TAX or/and GST when earning on-demand economy? 					\n					<p>The Australian Government is fully supportive of participation in the on-demand economy and has introduced a number of protection laws for consumers, including taxation and GST. In general, just like other sources of employment, the on-demand economy is subject to taxation and GST. The Australian Tax Office has some helpful information about tax and the on-demand economy GST, to find out more, <a href=\"https://www.ato.gov.au/general/the-sharing-economy-and-tax/income-tax-and-GST-in-the-sharing-economy/\">CLICK HERE</a>. If you need more information, we then recommend you to contact your accountant or tax/financial adviser to assess your personal circumstances.</p><p>If we didn&#8217;t answer your question or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>\n		<p>If we didn\'t answer your question or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>		\n			<h2>Learn all about the Free Income Compatibility Check</h2>		\n												What is the Free Compatibility Check?					\n					<p>Our compatibility check is designed to match your personal circumstances with the opportunities that are most relevant to you. We have designed a short 14-question checklist to better understand your current personal and economic situation, e.g. Do you own a car? Do you like helping others? Etc. This short <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> takes just a minute to complete and it can identify all sorts of opportunities for you.</p>\n												Why should I complete a Free Compatibility Check?					\n					<p>Your answers from the <strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong> are matched with over hundreds of available opportunities to earn income in the on-demand economy. Once youve completed it, we will send you an email with your personalised and comprehensive list containing on-demand economy businesses that match your responses and situation. The results will help you to understand both the number and dollar value associated with the available on-demand earning opportunities available to you through the 4Retirees community. We match people with opportunities and this mix changes all the time. We will update you as new businesses appear and/or if new questions are added to the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>. Results are processed automatically, in real time and personalised specifically for you, based on your answers to the survey questions.</p>\n												Who should take the Free Compatibility Check?					\n					<p>We believe that anyone who is the least bit interested in earning additional income should take part in the on-demand economy, and therefore should take our <strong><a href=\"#FICC\">Free Compatibility Check</a>.</strong> The on-demand economy is here to stay and is expected to represent the new world of work for generations to come. Why shouldnt you take advantage of these opportunities too? To participate in the on-demand economy you need to be at least 18 years old. We are the business that proudly supports retirees and their desire to stay relevant. We connect retirees with on-demand income opportunities as it can be difficult for you to identify these businesses with fast moving technologies and it may require advance research techniques that you just dont have access to. We want to make it simple for you. So, this <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> is available and open for you and almost anyone else in Australia who would like to earn on demand income. So feel free to recommend this <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> to your friends and family no matter of their age or status.</p>\n												How does the Free Compatibility Check work?					\n					<p>We have developed an online digital matching tool that asks you 14 short questions, and then utilises a rating and matching system to present you with opportunities suitable to your circumstance. We match you with available on-demand economy opportunities in real time. We believe we can provide you with a 98% match compatible with you. With your personalised <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>On-Demand Opportunities List </strong></a>you choose whats the most relevant and best fit for you at the current time. We intentionally dont promise a 100% match, as your individual circumstances can change daily and we might not be privileged to any of your personal information that might disqualify you from the participation e.g. the year of your vehicle, suspension of your driving license, etc.</p>\n												How much does the On-Demand Opportunities List cost?					\n					<p>To understand your opportunities and earnings potential, you can simply take our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>. Once you understand the number and scope of these earnings opportunities, you then make a decision if you would like to purchase the personalised and comprehensive <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List </strong>for a one-time cost of $149AUD. After your on time payment we will continue update you as new businesses appear and/or if new category questions are added to the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>, all of that will be done for you on an ongoing basis and for free.</p>\n												How do I decide whether or not to buy my personalised and comprehensive On-Demand Opportunities List?					\n					<p>This is certainly up to you. Its your personal decision to buy or not to buy this opportunity list. We want to create great experiences as well as opportunities. Only you are aware of your own wants, needs, and situation. We suggest using the common sense and good judgement that got you this far. Every situation is different. For instance, if the results only matches you with one or two opportunities of total possible earnings, $200, its probably not worth purchasing yet. However, if your results match you with 10 to 20 or more businesses and your total earning could be as much as $1,800 a month or upwards of $20,000 a year, then this could be a terrific investment as it represents a number of potentially profitable opportunities for you. </p>\n												What should I expect to get once I buy my personalised On-Demand Opportunities List? 					\n					<p>You will get a list of the individual businesses that your current personal circumstances have been matched with. The list can be as long as 100 businesses or more. It all depends on the answers you provided in our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> and the matching opportunities available. The list will contain business name, conditions of participation, terms of use, how to start, how much you can earn from each individual business and sometimes, we even have deals or special codes for you to quote when signing up with specific businesses. Each of these businesses have a helpful customer service team that will assist you in the sign up process and/or answer any questions you might have about getting started. The faster you sign up and work, the faster you can start earning.</p>\n												Do I need any professional qualifications for the participation in these on-demand jobs?					\n					<p>The quick answer is that you dont need to have them, but if you do, then this can help you take even more advantage on demand opportunities e.g if you are an accountant or writer or teacher etc. From what we have researched you dont need any high-level special qualifications or university degrees to participate in many current on-demand economy jobs. Once you get your personalised<strong> On-Demand Opportunities List</strong> we will provide you with information and links to each business terms of use and conditions to ensure you understand all requirements of each business individually. Each of these on-demand economy businesses operate individually and have their own process and list of qualifications youll need to supply before you start earning. We dont know what the future holdsit could have opportunities for on-demand doctors, and then, lets hope theyre required to have professional qualifications!</p>\n												Are there any special requirements to sign up with on-demand businesses?					\n					<p>Once you get your<strong> On-Demand Opportunities List</strong>, you will then be responsible for familiarising yourself with each business on your list, and their requirements. You are also responsible for everything between signing up and starting to earn. Each of these businesses operate individually and have a different sign-up process as well as requirements, documents, or information that you will have to provide. And each of these business have a helpful customer service team to assist you with the process and/or answer any questions you may have.</p>\n												How often should I take the Free Compatibility Check?					\n					<p>We believe you should take the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> once, and get a fully personalised and comprehensive <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List</strong>. We will monitor the changes in the on-demand economy in the background, looking to identify new opportunities regularly. If we make significant changes to the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>and/or introduce more on-demand economy business opportunities, we will notify you about those changes via email and explain how to get access to them. You will continue to get access, through your account with 4Retirees, to any new opportunities that are a match, and you wont pay any more than the original cost. Its a one-time payment that continues to give you access to the latest information and options that are suitable for you.</p>\n												Who is responsible for signing up with these on-demand economy businesses?					\n					<p>Once you take the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> and then decide to buy your personalised <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List</strong>, you will be responsible for becoming familiar with your matched opportunities. You can pick and choose one at a time or simply try to sign up with all of them straight away yourself. Each of these businesses operate individually and have different sign up processes and requirements. They also have a helpful customer service team to assist you with sign up and/or any questions you might have. Its up to you to decide how many businesses and how quickly you want to sign up to start earning. You will also receive a number of helpful tips from us via email to assist you with starting to earn straightaway. But, there is no obligation. If you purchased your list and decide that you dont want to pursue any opportunities on it that is perfectly fine and completely up to you.</p>\n												Is this personalised and comprehensive On-Demand Opportunities List relevant to my friends or family, can I share with them?					\n					<p>The list is personalised to you and your current, personal circumstance. So, we strongly advise you not to share it with your friends and family as they might have very different circumstances and eligibility criteria. Neither you nor 4Retirees wants to be seen as potentially misleading them. We would highly recommend that you send our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> to your friends and family to take it for themselves. Then they can check their own compatibility, see their own individual opportunities, and decide for themselves whether or not to take the next step.</p>\n												How much, as a retiree, can I earn in addition to my pension? 					\n					<p>The Australian Government has introduced taxation and conditions for retirees relating to the on-demand economy. Please visit this Government page and learn about your individual earnings strategies and also contact your accountant or tax/financial advisor to discuss further strategies to maximise your earning potential and understand the implications to your pension and taxes. To learn more from government <a href=\"https://www.ato.gov.au/general/the-sharing-economy-and-tax/income-tax-and-GST-in-the-sharing-economy/\">CLICK HERE</a>.</p>\n												Do I need to have an Australian Business Number (ABN) or any special types of insurance? 					\n					<p>Each on-demand economy business has their own requirements and sign up criteria. Some may require an ABN or insurance, but most of them will just require your Tax File number to track your earnings. We recommend you read the FAQs and the terms and conditions for each of the businesses you are considering working with before you start. If you are planning to share or rent out your home, car, or other valuable personal items, then you may find it helpful to discuss the situation with your insurer as well.</p>\n												What happens when some of the options I have matched with on my On-Demand Opportunities List arent servicing my particular area?					\n					<p>The on-demand economy is fast growing, so if the option that interests you isnt servicing your area yet, hopefully, it will soon. We recommend that you speak with the businesses of your particular interest and see if they have any plans to grow in your area, as most of them are continuing to expand. We do our best to give you different options for the same category in an attempt to minimise that problem for you, but we appreciate that it does exist. And, we continue to add additional on-demand businesses as fast as we can.</p>\n												The options that you have listed in my On-Demand Opportunities List are unfamiliar to me  what should I do?					\n					<p>Most on-demand economy businesses listed are small and medium-sized businesses. Brand awareness increase very gradually; It takes a long time for everyone to hear about such brands or discover their need for them. One of the advantages you have is that you are aware of these opportunities now, before they become mainstream. Take the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> and see what is on the offer, and if it is a good fit for you, you may be one of the pioneers in a whole new business!</p>\n		<p>If we didn\'t answer your question or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>		\n			<h2>Work With Us </h2>		\n		<p>If youre interested in a career that helps retired people make the most of their experience, youve come to the right place.</p><p>Were always on the lookout for talented, experienced and enthusiastic people like you. Its an opportunity to join our start up at an early stage and play a part in shaping its success.</p><p>We are offering both volunteer and paid work (part time and flexible arrangements, working remotely or from your home). Does this sound like a good opportunity for you? Contact us at <a href=\"mailto:career@4retirees.com\">career@4retirees.com</a></p>		\n			<h2>Feedback</h2>		\n		<p>4Retirees welcomes your suggestions, your feedback, including complaints. We believe people have a right to speak up, as it helps us to see what works for you, what doesn\'t, and where we can make improvements to provide you with a better opportunities and a better service. Your opinion matters, email us at <a href=\"mailto:feedback@4retirees.com\">feedback@4retirees.com</a></p>','Support Centre','','inherit','closed','closed','','56-revision-v1','','','2018-09-19 13:59:42','2018-09-19 04:29:42','',56,'http://4retirees.com/uncategorised/56-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(120,1,'2018-09-19 14:06:13','2018-09-19 04:36:13','<p><a href=\"#FAQ\">FAQs</a>   <a href=\"#work\">Work With Us</a>   <a href=\"#feedback\">Feedback</a></p>		\n										<img src=\"http://4retirees.com/wp-content/uploads/elementor/thumbs/Support4Retirees-nwagg5eism1odj408eme6w8dn2vsry4lbfxghepczk.png\" title=\"Support4Retirees\" alt=\"Support4Retirees\" />											\n		<p>If you have questions, we want to answer them. The following answers a number of frequently asked questions weve already identified. So have a read and if your question hasnt been answered here or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>		\n										<img width=\"528\" height=\"353\" src=\"http://4retirees.com/wp-content/uploads/Support4Retirees-Banner-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://4retirees.com/wp-content/uploads/Support4Retirees-Banner-1.jpg 528w, http://4retirees.com/wp-content/uploads/Support4Retirees-Banner-1-150x100.jpg 150w, http://4retirees.com/wp-content/uploads/Support4Retirees-Banner-1-300x201.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 528px) 100vw, 528px\" />											\n			<h2>Learn all about 4Retirees\n</h2>		\n												What is 4retirees?					\n					<p>4Retirees is a purpose-built community for retirees. Its a place where experience meets opportunity. 4Retirees was created with one clear focus; to help retirees easily take advantage of a new world of opportunities. Its a meeting place of ideas, inspiration, and experienced people. One of those opportunities is the online and on-demand economy that offers a new way to future-proof your retirement dreams. This new way of working lets you earn additional income while still maintaining the freedom to do the things you love most. No one knows better than a retiree how much the world can change in a lifetime. And 4Retirees is the network that helps you keep up with and benefit from those changesall at a pace youre comfortable with.</p>\n												Do I have to be tech-savvy to use 4Retirees?					\n					<p>No. 4Retirees is run for retirees, by retirees. Weve made it easy for you to get started. If you can read and tap on a keyboard, you can participate now and take our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>. And, when youre ready to learn some new technology skills, well be there too. Our aim is to help you to keep pace with this burgeoning economy and part of that is upskilling your technology skills. These improved skills will help you to unlock a future filled with more opportunities for earning income, taking advantage of tools available to you, so that you can live your dream retirement life and keep you better connected to your friends, family, and the rest of the world.</p>\n												Who participates in 4Retirees community?					\n					<p>Anyone who is chasing a dream of freedom is participating in the 4Retirees community. Anyone who is thinking of career change to enable their potential and opportunities can participate in our community and take advantage of whats on offer. If you have an interest in the on-demand economy, we invite you to start your journey here by taking our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check.</strong></a></p>\n												In what ways will I be able to connect with other retirees?  					\n					<p>Our vision is to build a better place for all retirees. Our big goal at first is to bring you all together and to establish the connections. We know that people do business and learn from people they know, like, and trust. So, first things first, well concentrate on providing opportunities to come together so we can all benefit the advantage of the technology and the on-demand economy. We want to create a community of retirees4retirees, eventually we can co-create, build a better place with a better economy where all retirees come to connect, interact, meet, help each other, share their skills, build new ones, volunteer, earn money, and maybe even make some friends! We will provide you soon with opportunities to participate in forums, to connect, chat, share ideas, and ask questions about your fellow community members. You can also connect with the community through most of our social media channels. Make sure to sign up for our eNewsletter so we keep you up to date on our progress as our community grows and becomes an even better place for retirees.</p>\n												How do I manage my subscription preferences?					\n					<p>Once you take our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> or sign up to our eNewsletter, we will create an account for you and send you link to activate via email. You can manage your preferences by accessing right top corner of your account under the button that says &#8216;<a href=\"http://4retirees.com/my-account\" data-wplink-url-error=\"true\">Login</a>&#8216; or <a href=\"http://4retirees.com/my-account\" data-wplink-url-error=\"true\">My account</a>. If you would like to receive our weekly eNewsletter with useful tips and hints, or perhaps you would like to update your interest information so that we can provide you with more comprehensive updates weekly, you can do all of that in through your account preferences.</p>\n												I forgot my password, how do I reset it?					\n					<p>You can manage this under your account &#8211; right top corner &#8211; you can request a password reset, or before you login, reset by clicking on <a href=\"http://4retirees.com/wp-login.php?action=lostpassword\" data-wplink-url-error=\"true\">forgot my password</a>.</p>\n												How do I deactivate my account? 					\n					<p>We would certainly be sorry to see you go, but if you really want to, you can simply unsubscribe from all the communication or you can deactivate your account. You can manage these preferences under the <a href=\"http://4retirees.com/my-account\" data-wplink-url-error=\"true\">My Account</a> tab located in the right top corner, through the button, Deactivate Account.</p>\n		<p>If we didn\'t answer your question or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>		\n			<h2>Learn all about on-demand economy</h2>		\n												What exactly is the on-demand economy?					\n					<p>The on-demand economy is defined as the economic activity created by technology companies that fulfil consumer demand via the immediate provisioning of goods and services. The on-demand economy, also known as a sharing economy or collaborative consumption or the peer economy, is a trending business concept that highlights the ability (and perhaps the preference) of individuals to rent or borrow goods or services and not necessarily buy and own them. Owners rent out something they are not using, such as a car, house, bicycle, or their skills, to someone else using these peer-to-peer services and earning money on demand.</p>\n												Can you give me some examples of businesses in the on-demand economy? 					\n					<p>We have a comprehensive list of over hundreds of on-demand economy businesses right here in Australia. Two that you have most likely heard of are UBER and Airbnb. With UBER, people use their own cars, sign up as drivers, and then transport people or deliver food to other people as part of their peer-to-peer network. You can work on your terms, the hours you want, in the area you want, and still earn money while meeting new people and listening to your favourite radio station. The second example is Airbnb. It is an online marketplace and hospitality service for people to lease or rent short-term lodging including holiday cottages, rooms, apartments, homestays, hostel beds, etc. You can do this all year long if you have a place you never use, for weeks at a time when you are travelling, or just until you find new tenants for your investment property. Its a great contemporary (and cheaper) alternative to hotel accommodation. We can match you with hundreds of these types of businessesthe choice of businesses participating in the on-demand economy is virtually endless and new ones are popping up all the time. Youll be able to find transportation, hobby-related businesses, travel, education, business services, delivery, pet care, and the works!</p>\n												Why is the on-demand economy growing so fast?					\n					<p>The <strong>on-demand economy </strong>is here to stay. And its growth is a given. Whether its renting a room, hiring a driver, renting a parking space, or outsourcing household tasks, the sharing economy is disrupting a range of industries and causing regulators to take note. Technology is making it easier for new marketplaces to be created. Services that used to be high touch, slow to deliver, but yet expensive are now fast and efficient, thanks to technology like smart phones. This creates a better experience for the consumer and also the person providing the service. Australia has a supportive start-up community with new businesses starting up all the time, and we are here to provide you with this comprehensive research in discovering new options for earning an income all the time. Its an incredibly exciting time!</p>\n												How can I start earning money in the on-demand economy? 					\n					<p>The first step is to understand your compatibility with the opportunities available. Take our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> and see if your current circumstances match any of these on-demand businesses and how much you could potentially earn. Once you receive your results, then you decide if it makes sense for you to purchase access to your custom <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List </strong>so that you can then pursue your matching income-generating opportunities.</p>\n												How much I can get paid from the on-demand economy? 					\n					<p>Once you buy your personalised and comprehensive <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List</strong>, you can explore each individual opportunity you matched with, sign up to do it, start working, and start earning from your very first day. In the on-demand economy, you have the potential to earn per hour, per day, per week, or per item or project. Its possible to earn anywhere from $20 per hour to thousands of dollarsor moreper week or per month. Your earning potential depends on your skill set, situation, the opportunities available, and how little or how much youre prepared to do. The choice is yours! And, youre not locked into committing to any time frames. You can dip in or out when it makes sense for you.</p>\n												How do I get paid from these individual on-demand economy businesses?					\n					<p>Each of these businesses have their own individual payment systems and conditions that you should review before signing up. Payment is usually made directly to your bank account or PayPal account. Fast payment is one of the benefits of the on-demand economy. After you have provided a service via one of the on-demand economy businesses, some payments are received within 1-3 business days, others or on a designated day each week or month. We definitely recommend that you to check this with each business before you start. And, we recommend speaking with your accountant or tax/financial adviser about your individual circumstances.</p>\n												Is the on-demand economy legal?					\n					<p>The on-demand economy and participation in it is most definitely legal and it is even supported by Australian Government. You, as a participant in it, are fully supported by Australian Consumer Law while using the on-demand sharing economy. To find out more, <a href=\"http://consumerlaw.gov.au/business-and-the-acl/sharing-economy-platforms/\">CLICK HERE</a>.</p>\n												Do I pay TAX or/and GST when earning on-demand economy? 					\n					<p>The Australian Government is fully supportive of participation in the on-demand economy and has introduced a number of protection laws for consumers, including taxation and GST. In general, just like other sources of employment, the on-demand economy is subject to taxation and GST. The Australian Tax Office has some helpful information about tax and the on-demand economy GST, to find out more, <a href=\"https://www.ato.gov.au/general/the-sharing-economy-and-tax/income-tax-and-GST-in-the-sharing-economy/\">CLICK HERE</a>. If you need more information, we then recommend you to contact your accountant or tax/financial adviser to assess your personal circumstances.</p><p>If we didn&#8217;t answer your question or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>\n		<p>If we didn\'t answer your question or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>		\n			<h2>Learn all about the Free Income Compatibility Check</h2>		\n												What is the Free Compatibility Check?					\n					<p>Our compatibility check is designed to match your personal circumstances with the opportunities that are most relevant to you. We have designed a short 14-question checklist to better understand your current personal and economic situation, e.g. Do you own a car? Do you like helping others? Etc. This short <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> takes just a minute to complete and it can identify all sorts of opportunities for you.</p>\n												Why should I complete a Free Compatibility Check?					\n					<p>Your answers from the <strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong> are matched with over hundreds of available opportunities to earn income in the on-demand economy. Once youve completed it, we will send you an email with your personalised and comprehensive list containing on-demand economy businesses that match your responses and situation. The results will help you to understand both the number and dollar value associated with the available on-demand earning opportunities available to you through the 4Retirees community. We match people with opportunities and this mix changes all the time. We will update you as new businesses appear and/or if new questions are added to the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>. Results are processed automatically, in real time and personalised specifically for you, based on your answers to the survey questions.</p>\n												Who should take the Free Compatibility Check?					\n					<p>We believe that anyone who is the least bit interested in earning additional income should take part in the on-demand economy, and therefore should take our <strong><a href=\"#FICC\">Free Compatibility Check</a>.</strong> The on-demand economy is here to stay and is expected to represent the new world of work for generations to come. Why shouldnt you take advantage of these opportunities too? To participate in the on-demand economy you need to be at least 18 years old. We are the business that proudly supports retirees and their desire to stay relevant. We connect retirees with on-demand income opportunities as it can be difficult for you to identify these businesses with fast moving technologies and it may require advance research techniques that you just dont have access to. We want to make it simple for you. So, this <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> is available and open for you and almost anyone else in Australia who would like to earn on demand income. So feel free to recommend this <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> to your friends and family no matter of their age or status.</p>\n												How does the Free Compatibility Check work?					\n					<p>We have developed an online digital matching tool that asks you 14 short questions, and then utilises a rating and matching system to present you with opportunities suitable to your circumstance. We match you with available on-demand economy opportunities in real time. We believe we can provide you with a 98% match compatible with you. With your personalised <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>On-Demand Opportunities List </strong></a>you choose whats the most relevant and best fit for you at the current time. We intentionally dont promise a 100% match, as your individual circumstances can change daily and we might not be privileged to any of your personal information that might disqualify you from the participation e.g. the year of your vehicle, suspension of your driving license, etc.</p>\n												How much does the On-Demand Opportunities List cost?					\n					<p>To understand your opportunities and earnings potential, you can simply take our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>. Once you understand the number and scope of these earnings opportunities, you then make a decision if you would like to purchase the personalised and comprehensive <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List </strong>for a one-time cost of $149AUD. After your on time payment we will continue update you as new businesses appear and/or if new category questions are added to the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>, all of that will be done for you on an ongoing basis and for free.</p>\n												How do I decide whether or not to buy my personalised and comprehensive On-Demand Opportunities List?					\n					<p>This is certainly up to you. Its your personal decision to buy or not to buy this opportunity list. We want to create great experiences as well as opportunities. Only you are aware of your own wants, needs, and situation. We suggest using the common sense and good judgement that got you this far. Every situation is different. For instance, if the results only matches you with one or two opportunities of total possible earnings, $200, its probably not worth purchasing yet. However, if your results match you with 10 to 20 or more businesses and your total earning could be as much as $1,800 a month or upwards of $20,000 a year, then this could be a terrific investment as it represents a number of potentially profitable opportunities for you. </p>\n												What should I expect to get once I buy my personalised On-Demand Opportunities List? 					\n					<p>You will get a list of the individual businesses that your current personal circumstances have been matched with. The list can be as long as 100 businesses or more. It all depends on the answers you provided in our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> and the matching opportunities available. The list will contain business name, conditions of participation, terms of use, how to start, how much you can earn from each individual business and sometimes, we even have deals or special codes for you to quote when signing up with specific businesses. Each of these businesses have a helpful customer service team that will assist you in the sign up process and/or answer any questions you might have about getting started. The faster you sign up and work, the faster you can start earning.</p>\n												Do I need any professional qualifications for the participation in these on-demand jobs?					\n					<p>The quick answer is that you dont need to have them, but if you do, then this can help you take even more advantage on demand opportunities e.g if you are an accountant or writer or teacher etc. From what we have researched you dont need any high-level special qualifications or university degrees to participate in many current on-demand economy jobs. Once you get your personalised<strong> On-Demand Opportunities List</strong> we will provide you with information and links to each business terms of use and conditions to ensure you understand all requirements of each business individually. Each of these on-demand economy businesses operate individually and have their own process and list of qualifications youll need to supply before you start earning. We dont know what the future holdsit could have opportunities for on-demand doctors, and then, lets hope theyre required to have professional qualifications!</p>\n												Are there any special requirements to sign up with on-demand businesses?					\n					<p>Once you get your<strong> On-Demand Opportunities List</strong>, you will then be responsible for familiarising yourself with each business on your list, and their requirements. You are also responsible for everything between signing up and starting to earn. Each of these businesses operate individually and have a different sign-up process as well as requirements, documents, or information that you will have to provide. And each of these business have a helpful customer service team to assist you with the process and/or answer any questions you may have.</p>\n												How often should I take the Free Compatibility Check?					\n					<p>We believe you should take the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> once, and get a fully personalised and comprehensive <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List</strong>. We will monitor the changes in the on-demand economy in the background, looking to identify new opportunities regularly. If we make significant changes to the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>and/or introduce more on-demand economy business opportunities, we will notify you about those changes via email and explain how to get access to them. You will continue to get access, through your account with 4Retirees, to any new opportunities that are a match, and you wont pay any more than the original cost. Its a one-time payment that continues to give you access to the latest information and options that are suitable for you.</p>\n												Who is responsible for signing up with these on-demand economy businesses?					\n					<p>Once you take the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> and then decide to buy your personalised <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List</strong>, you will be responsible for becoming familiar with your matched opportunities. You can pick and choose one at a time or simply try to sign up with all of them straight away yourself. Each of these businesses operate individually and have different sign up processes and requirements. They also have a helpful customer service team to assist you with sign up and/or any questions you might have. Its up to you to decide how many businesses and how quickly you want to sign up to start earning. You will also receive a number of helpful tips from us via email to assist you with starting to earn straightaway. But, there is no obligation. If you purchased your list and decide that you dont want to pursue any opportunities on it that is perfectly fine and completely up to you.</p>\n												Is this personalised and comprehensive On-Demand Opportunities List relevant to my friends or family, can I share with them?					\n					<p>The list is personalised to you and your current, personal circumstance. So, we strongly advise you not to share it with your friends and family as they might have very different circumstances and eligibility criteria. Neither you nor 4Retirees wants to be seen as potentially misleading them. We would highly recommend that you send our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> to your friends and family to take it for themselves. Then they can check their own compatibility, see their own individual opportunities, and decide for themselves whether or not to take the next step.</p>\n												How much, as a retiree, can I earn in addition to my pension? 					\n					<p>The Australian Government has introduced taxation and conditions for retirees relating to the on-demand economy. Please visit this Government page and learn about your individual earnings strategies and also contact your accountant or tax/financial advisor to discuss further strategies to maximise your earning potential and understand the implications to your pension and taxes. To learn more from government <a href=\"https://www.ato.gov.au/general/the-sharing-economy-and-tax/income-tax-and-GST-in-the-sharing-economy/\">CLICK HERE</a>.</p>\n												Do I need to have an Australian Business Number (ABN) or any special types of insurance? 					\n					<p>Each on-demand economy business has their own requirements and sign up criteria. Some may require an ABN or insurance, but most of them will just require your Tax File number to track your earnings. We recommend you read the FAQs and the terms and conditions for each of the businesses you are considering working with before you start. If you are planning to share or rent out your home, car, or other valuable personal items, then you may find it helpful to discuss the situation with your insurer as well.</p>\n												What happens when some of the options I have matched with on my On-Demand Opportunities List arent servicing my particular area?					\n					<p>The on-demand economy is fast growing, so if the option that interests you isnt servicing your area yet, hopefully, it will soon. We recommend that you speak with the businesses of your particular interest and see if they have any plans to grow in your area, as most of them are continuing to expand. We do our best to give you different options for the same category in an attempt to minimise that problem for you, but we appreciate that it does exist. And, we continue to add additional on-demand businesses as fast as we can.</p>\n												The options that you have listed in my On-Demand Opportunities List are unfamiliar to me  what should I do?					\n					<p>Most on-demand economy businesses listed are small and medium-sized businesses. Brand awareness increase very gradually; It takes a long time for everyone to hear about such brands or discover their need for them. One of the advantages you have is that you are aware of these opportunities now, before they become mainstream. Take the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> and see what is on the offer, and if it is a good fit for you, you may be one of the pioneers in a whole new business!</p>\n		<p>If we didn\'t answer your question or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>		\n			<h2>Work With Us </h2>		\n		<p>If youre interested in a career that helps retired people make the most of their experience, youve come to the right place.</p><p>Were always on the lookout for talented, experienced and enthusiastic people like you. Its an opportunity to join our start up at an early stage and play a part in shaping its success.</p><p>We are offering both volunteer and paid work (part time and flexible arrangements, working remotely or from your home). Does this sound like a good opportunity for you? Contact us at <a href=\"mailto:career@4retirees.com\">career@4retirees.com</a></p>		\n			<h2>Feedback</h2>		\n		<p>4Retirees welcomes your suggestions, your feedback, including complaints. We believe people have a right to speak up, as it helps us to see what works for you, what doesn\'t, and where we can make improvements to provide you with a better opportunities and a better service. Your opinion matters, email us at <a href=\"mailto:feedback@4retirees.com\">feedback@4retirees.com</a></p>','Support Centre','','inherit','closed','closed','','56-revision-v1','','','2018-09-19 14:06:13','2018-09-19 04:36:13','',56,'http://4retirees.com/uncategorised/56-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(121,1,'2018-09-19 14:08:06','2018-09-19 04:38:06','<p><a href=\"#FAQ\">FAQs</a>   <a href=\"#work\">Work With Us</a>   <a href=\"#feedback\">Feedback</a></p>		\n										<img src=\"http://4retirees.com/wp-content/uploads/elementor/thumbs/Support4Retirees-nwagg5eism1odj408eme6w8dn2vsry4lbfxghepczk.png\" title=\"Support4Retirees\" alt=\"Support4Retirees\" />											\n		<p>If you have questions, we want to answer them. The following answers a number of frequently asked questions weve already identified. So have a read and if your question hasnt been answered here or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>		\n										<img width=\"528\" height=\"353\" src=\"http://4retirees.com/wp-content/uploads/Support4Retirees-Banner-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://4retirees.com/wp-content/uploads/Support4Retirees-Banner-1.jpg 528w, http://4retirees.com/wp-content/uploads/Support4Retirees-Banner-1-150x100.jpg 150w, http://4retirees.com/wp-content/uploads/Support4Retirees-Banner-1-300x201.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 528px) 100vw, 528px\" />											\n			<h2>Learn all about 4Retirees\n</h2>		\n												What is 4retirees?					\n					<p>4Retirees is a purpose-built community for retirees. Its a place where experience meets opportunity. 4Retirees was created with one clear focus; to help retirees easily take advantage of a new world of opportunities. Its a meeting place of ideas, inspiration, and experienced people. One of those opportunities is the online and on-demand economy that offers a new way to future-proof your retirement dreams. This new way of working lets you earn additional income while still maintaining the freedom to do the things you love most. No one knows better than a retiree how much the world can change in a lifetime. And 4Retirees is the network that helps you keep up with and benefit from those changesall at a pace youre comfortable with.</p>\n												Do I have to be tech-savvy to use 4Retirees?					\n					<p>No. 4Retirees is run for retirees, by retirees. Weve made it easy for you to get started. If you can read and tap on a keyboard, you can participate now and take our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>. And, when youre ready to learn some new technology skills, well be there too. Our aim is to help you to keep pace with this burgeoning economy and part of that is upskilling your technology skills. These improved skills will help you to unlock a future filled with more opportunities for earning income, taking advantage of tools available to you, so that you can live your dream retirement life and keep you better connected to your friends, family, and the rest of the world.</p>\n												Who participates in 4Retirees community?					\n					<p>Anyone who is chasing a dream of freedom is participating in the 4Retirees community. Anyone who is thinking of career change to enable their potential and opportunities can participate in our community and take advantage of whats on offer. If you have an interest in the on-demand economy, we invite you to start your journey here by taking our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check.</strong></a></p>\n												In what ways will I be able to connect with other retirees?  					\n					<p>Our vision is to build a better place for all retirees. Our big goal at first is to bring you all together and to establish the connections. We know that people do business and learn from people they know, like, and trust. So, first things first, well concentrate on providing opportunities to come together so we can all benefit the advantage of the technology and the on-demand economy. We want to create a community of retirees4retirees, eventually we can co-create, build a better place with a better economy where all retirees come to connect, interact, meet, help each other, share their skills, build new ones, volunteer, earn money, and maybe even make some friends! We will provide you soon with opportunities to participate in forums, to connect, chat, share ideas, and ask questions about your fellow community members. You can also connect with the community through most of our social media channels. Make sure to sign up for our eNewsletter so we keep you up to date on our progress as our community grows and becomes an even better place for retirees.</p>\n												How do I manage my subscription preferences?					\n					<p>Once you take our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> or sign up to our eNewsletter, we will create an account for you and send you link to activate via email. You can manage your preferences by accessing right top corner of your account under the button that says &#8216;<a href=\"http://4retirees.com/my-account\" data-wplink-url-error=\"true\">Login</a>&#8216; or <a href=\"http://4retirees.com/my-account\" data-wplink-url-error=\"true\">My account</a>. If you would like to receive our weekly eNewsletter with useful tips and hints, or perhaps you would like to update your interest information so that we can provide you with more comprehensive updates weekly, you can do all of that in through your account preferences.</p>\n												I forgot my password, how do I reset it?					\n					<p>You can manage this under your account &#8211; right top corner &#8211; you can request a password reset, or before you login, reset by clicking on <a href=\"http://4retirees.com/wp-login.php?action=lostpassword\" data-wplink-url-error=\"true\">forgot my password</a>.</p>\n												How do I deactivate my account? 					\n					<p>We would certainly be sorry to see you go, but if you really want to, you can simply unsubscribe from all the communication or you can deactivate your account. You can manage these preferences under the <a href=\"http://4retirees.com/my-account\" data-wplink-url-error=\"true\">My Account</a> tab located in the right top corner, through the button, Deactivate Account.</p>\n		<p>If we didn\'t answer your question or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>		\n			<h2>Learn all about on-demand economy</h2>		\n												What exactly is the on-demand economy?					\n					<p>The on-demand economy is defined as the economic activity created by technology companies that fulfil consumer demand via the immediate provisioning of goods and services. The on-demand economy, also known as a sharing economy or collaborative consumption or the peer economy, is a trending business concept that highlights the ability (and perhaps the preference) of individuals to rent or borrow goods or services and not necessarily buy and own them. Owners rent out something they are not using, such as a car, house, bicycle, or their skills, to someone else using these peer-to-peer services and earning money on demand.</p>\n												Can you give me some examples of businesses in the on-demand economy? 					\n					<p>We have a comprehensive list of over hundreds of on-demand economy businesses right here in Australia. Two that you have most likely heard of are UBER and Airbnb. With UBER, people use their own cars, sign up as drivers, and then transport people or deliver food to other people as part of their peer-to-peer network. You can work on your terms, the hours you want, in the area you want, and still earn money while meeting new people and listening to your favourite radio station. The second example is Airbnb. It is an online marketplace and hospitality service for people to lease or rent short-term lodging including holiday cottages, rooms, apartments, homestays, hostel beds, etc. You can do this all year long if you have a place you never use, for weeks at a time when you are travelling, or just until you find new tenants for your investment property. Its a great contemporary (and cheaper) alternative to hotel accommodation. We can match you with hundreds of these types of businessesthe choice of businesses participating in the on-demand economy is virtually endless and new ones are popping up all the time. Youll be able to find transportation, hobby-related businesses, travel, education, business services, delivery, pet care, and the works!</p>\n												Why is the on-demand economy growing so fast?					\n					<p>The <strong>on-demand economy </strong>is here to stay. And its growth is a given. Whether its renting a room, hiring a driver, renting a parking space, or outsourcing household tasks, the sharing economy is disrupting a range of industries and causing regulators to take note. Technology is making it easier for new marketplaces to be created. Services that used to be high touch, slow to deliver, but yet expensive are now fast and efficient, thanks to technology like smart phones. This creates a better experience for the consumer and also the person providing the service. Australia has a supportive start-up community with new businesses starting up all the time, and we are here to provide you with this comprehensive research in discovering new options for earning an income all the time. Its an incredibly exciting time!</p>\n												How can I start earning money in the on-demand economy? 					\n					<p>The first step is to understand your compatibility with the opportunities available. Take our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> and see if your current circumstances match any of these on-demand businesses and how much you could potentially earn. Once you receive your results, then you decide if it makes sense for you to purchase access to your custom <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List </strong>so that you can then pursue your matching income-generating opportunities.</p>\n												How much I can get paid from the on-demand economy? 					\n					<p>Once you buy your personalised and comprehensive <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List</strong>, you can explore each individual opportunity you matched with, sign up to do it, start working, and start earning from your very first day. In the on-demand economy, you have the potential to earn per hour, per day, per week, or per item or project. Its possible to earn anywhere from $20 per hour to thousands of dollarsor moreper week or per month. Your earning potential depends on your skill set, situation, the opportunities available, and how little or how much youre prepared to do. The choice is yours! And, youre not locked into committing to any time frames. You can dip in or out when it makes sense for you.</p>\n												How do I get paid from these individual on-demand economy businesses?					\n					<p>Each of these businesses have their own individual payment systems and conditions that you should review before signing up. Payment is usually made directly to your bank account or PayPal account. Fast payment is one of the benefits of the on-demand economy. After you have provided a service via one of the on-demand economy businesses, some payments are received within 1-3 business days, others or on a designated day each week or month. We definitely recommend that you to check this with each business before you start. And, we recommend speaking with your accountant or tax/financial adviser about your individual circumstances.</p>\n												Is the on-demand economy legal?					\n					<p>The on-demand economy and participation in it is most definitely legal and it is even supported by Australian Government. You, as a participant in it, are fully supported by Australian Consumer Law while using the on-demand sharing economy. To find out more, <a href=\"http://consumerlaw.gov.au/business-and-the-acl/sharing-economy-platforms/\">CLICK HERE</a>.</p>\n												Do I pay TAX or/and GST when earning on-demand economy? 					\n					<p>The Australian Government is fully supportive of participation in the on-demand economy and has introduced a number of protection laws for consumers, including taxation and GST. In general, just like other sources of employment, the on-demand economy is subject to taxation and GST. The Australian Tax Office has some helpful information about tax and the on-demand economy GST, to find out more, <a href=\"https://www.ato.gov.au/general/the-sharing-economy-and-tax/income-tax-and-GST-in-the-sharing-economy/\">CLICK HERE</a>. If you need more information, we then recommend you to contact your accountant or tax/financial adviser to assess your personal circumstances.</p><p>If we didn&#8217;t answer your question or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>\n		<p>If we didn\'t answer your question or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>		\n			<h2>Learn all about the Free Income Compatibility Check</h2>		\n												What is the Free Compatibility Check?					\n					<p>Our compatibility check is designed to match your personal circumstances with the opportunities that are most relevant to you. We have designed a short 14-question checklist to better understand your current personal and economic situation, e.g. Do you own a car? Do you like helping others? Etc. This short <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> takes just a minute to complete and it can identify all sorts of opportunities for you.</p>\n												Why should I complete a Free Compatibility Check?					\n					<p>Your answers from the <strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong> are matched with over hundreds of available opportunities to earn income in the on-demand economy. Once youve completed it, we will send you an email with your personalised and comprehensive list containing on-demand economy businesses that match your responses and situation. The results will help you to understand both the number and dollar value associated with the available on-demand earning opportunities available to you through the 4Retirees community. We match people with opportunities and this mix changes all the time. We will update you as new businesses appear and/or if new questions are added to the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>. Results are processed automatically, in real time and personalised specifically for you, based on your answers to the survey questions.</p>\n												Who should take the Free Compatibility Check?					\n					<p>We believe that anyone who is the least bit interested in earning additional income should take part in the on-demand economy, and therefore should take our <strong><a href=\"#FICC\">Free Compatibility Check</a>.</strong> The on-demand economy is here to stay and is expected to represent the new world of work for generations to come. Why shouldnt you take advantage of these opportunities too? To participate in the on-demand economy you need to be at least 18 years old. We are the business that proudly supports retirees and their desire to stay relevant. We connect retirees with on-demand income opportunities as it can be difficult for you to identify these businesses with fast moving technologies and it may require advance research techniques that you just dont have access to. We want to make it simple for you. So, this <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> is available and open for you and almost anyone else in Australia who would like to earn on demand income. So feel free to recommend this <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> to your friends and family no matter of their age or status.</p>\n												How does the Free Compatibility Check work?					\n					<p>We have developed an online digital matching tool that asks you 14 short questions, and then utilises a rating and matching system to present you with opportunities suitable to your circumstance. We match you with available on-demand economy opportunities in real time. We believe we can provide you with a 98% match compatible with you. With your personalised <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>On-Demand Opportunities List </strong></a>you choose whats the most relevant and best fit for you at the current time. We intentionally dont promise a 100% match, as your individual circumstances can change daily and we might not be privileged to any of your personal information that might disqualify you from the participation e.g. the year of your vehicle, suspension of your driving license, etc.</p>\n												How much does the On-Demand Opportunities List cost?					\n					<p>To understand your opportunities and earnings potential, you can simply take our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>. Once you understand the number and scope of these earnings opportunities, you then make a decision if you would like to purchase the personalised and comprehensive <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List </strong>for a one-time cost of $149AUD. After your on time payment we will continue update you as new businesses appear and/or if new category questions are added to the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>, all of that will be done for you on an ongoing basis and for free.</p>\n												How do I decide whether or not to buy my personalised and comprehensive On-Demand Opportunities List?					\n					<p>This is certainly up to you. Its your personal decision to buy or not to buy this opportunity list. We want to create great experiences as well as opportunities. Only you are aware of your own wants, needs, and situation. We suggest using the common sense and good judgement that got you this far. Every situation is different. For instance, if the results only matches you with one or two opportunities of total possible earnings, $200, its probably not worth purchasing yet. However, if your results match you with 10 to 20 or more businesses and your total earning could be as much as $1,800 a month or upwards of $20,000 a year, then this could be a terrific investment as it represents a number of potentially profitable opportunities for you. </p>\n												What should I expect to get once I buy my personalised On-Demand Opportunities List? 					\n					<p>You will get a list of the individual businesses that your current personal circumstances have been matched with. The list can be as long as 100 businesses or more. It all depends on the answers you provided in our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> and the matching opportunities available. The list will contain business name, conditions of participation, terms of use, how to start, how much you can earn from each individual business and sometimes, we even have deals or special codes for you to quote when signing up with specific businesses. Each of these businesses have a helpful customer service team that will assist you in the sign up process and/or answer any questions you might have about getting started. The faster you sign up and work, the faster you can start earning.</p>\n												Do I need any professional qualifications for the participation in these on-demand jobs?					\n					<p>The quick answer is that you dont need to have them, but if you do, then this can help you take even more advantage on demand opportunities e.g if you are an accountant or writer or teacher etc. From what we have researched you dont need any high-level special qualifications or university degrees to participate in many current on-demand economy jobs. Once you get your personalised<strong> On-Demand Opportunities List</strong> we will provide you with information and links to each business terms of use and conditions to ensure you understand all requirements of each business individually. Each of these on-demand economy businesses operate individually and have their own process and list of qualifications youll need to supply before you start earning. We dont know what the future holdsit could have opportunities for on-demand doctors, and then, lets hope theyre required to have professional qualifications!</p>\n												Are there any special requirements to sign up with on-demand businesses?					\n					<p>Once you get your<strong> On-Demand Opportunities List</strong>, you will then be responsible for familiarising yourself with each business on your list, and their requirements. You are also responsible for everything between signing up and starting to earn. Each of these businesses operate individually and have a different sign-up process as well as requirements, documents, or information that you will have to provide. And each of these business have a helpful customer service team to assist you with the process and/or answer any questions you may have.</p>\n												How often should I take the Free Compatibility Check?					\n					<p>We believe you should take the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> once, and get a fully personalised and comprehensive <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List</strong>. We will monitor the changes in the on-demand economy in the background, looking to identify new opportunities regularly. If we make significant changes to the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>and/or introduce more on-demand economy business opportunities, we will notify you about those changes via email and explain how to get access to them. You will continue to get access, through your account with 4Retirees, to any new opportunities that are a match, and you wont pay any more than the original cost. Its a one-time payment that continues to give you access to the latest information and options that are suitable for you.</p>\n												Who is responsible for signing up with these on-demand economy businesses?					\n					<p>Once you take the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> and then decide to buy your personalised <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List</strong>, you will be responsible for becoming familiar with your matched opportunities. You can pick and choose one at a time or simply try to sign up with all of them straight away yourself. Each of these businesses operate individually and have different sign up processes and requirements. They also have a helpful customer service team to assist you with sign up and/or any questions you might have. Its up to you to decide how many businesses and how quickly you want to sign up to start earning. You will also receive a number of helpful tips from us via email to assist you with starting to earn straightaway. But, there is no obligation. If you purchased your list and decide that you dont want to pursue any opportunities on it that is perfectly fine and completely up to you.</p>\n												Is this personalised and comprehensive On-Demand Opportunities List relevant to my friends or family, can I share with them?					\n					<p>The list is personalised to you and your current, personal circumstance. So, we strongly advise you not to share it with your friends and family as they might have very different circumstances and eligibility criteria. Neither you nor 4Retirees wants to be seen as potentially misleading them. We would highly recommend that you send our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> to your friends and family to take it for themselves. Then they can check their own compatibility, see their own individual opportunities, and decide for themselves whether or not to take the next step.</p>\n												How much, as a retiree, can I earn in addition to my pension? 					\n					<p>The Australian Government has introduced taxation and conditions for retirees relating to the on-demand economy. Please visit this Government page and learn about your individual earnings strategies and also contact your accountant or tax/financial advisor to discuss further strategies to maximise your earning potential and understand the implications to your pension and taxes. To learn more from government <a href=\"https://www.ato.gov.au/general/the-sharing-economy-and-tax/income-tax-and-GST-in-the-sharing-economy/\">CLICK HERE</a>.</p>\n												Do I need to have an Australian Business Number (ABN) or any special types of insurance? 					\n					<p>Each on-demand economy business has their own requirements and sign up criteria. Some may require an ABN or insurance, but most of them will just require your Tax File number to track your earnings. We recommend you read the FAQs and the terms and conditions for each of the businesses you are considering working with before you start. If you are planning to share or rent out your home, car, or other valuable personal items, then you may find it helpful to discuss the situation with your insurer as well.</p>\n												What happens when some of the options I have matched with on my On-Demand Opportunities List arent servicing my particular area?					\n					<p>The on-demand economy is fast growing, so if the option that interests you isnt servicing your area yet, hopefully, it will soon. We recommend that you speak with the businesses of your particular interest and see if they have any plans to grow in your area, as most of them are continuing to expand. We do our best to give you different options for the same category in an attempt to minimise that problem for you, but we appreciate that it does exist. And, we continue to add additional on-demand businesses as fast as we can.</p>\n												The options that you have listed in my On-Demand Opportunities List are unfamiliar to me  what should I do?					\n					<p>Most on-demand economy businesses listed are small and medium-sized businesses. Brand awareness increase very gradually; It takes a long time for everyone to hear about such brands or discover their need for them. One of the advantages you have is that you are aware of these opportunities now, before they become mainstream. Take the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> and see what is on the offer, and if it is a good fit for you, you may be one of the pioneers in a whole new business!</p>\n		<p>If we didn\'t answer your question or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>		\n			<h2>Work With Us </h2>		\n		<p>If youre interested in a career that helps retired people make the most of their experience, youve come to the right place.</p><p>Were always on the lookout for talented, experienced and enthusiastic people like you. Its an opportunity to join our start up at an early stage and play a part in shaping its success.</p><p>We are offering both volunteer and paid work (part time and flexible arrangements, working remotely or from your home). Does this sound like a good opportunity for you? Contact us at <a href=\"mailto:career@4retirees.com\">career@4retirees.com</a></p>		\n			<h2>Feedback</h2>		\n		<p>4Retirees welcomes your suggestions, your feedback, including complaints. We believe people have a right to speak up, as it helps us to see what works for you, what doesn\'t, and where we can make improvements to provide you with a better opportunities and a better service. Your opinion matters, email us at <a href=\"mailto:feedback@4retirees.com\">feedback@4retirees.com</a></p>','Support Centre','','inherit','closed','closed','','56-revision-v1','','','2018-09-19 14:08:06','2018-09-19 04:38:06','',56,'http://4retirees.com/uncategorised/56-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(122,1,'2018-09-19 14:38:16','2018-09-19 05:08:16','<p><a href=\"#FAQ\">FAQs</a>   <a href=\"#work\">Work With Us</a>   <a href=\"#feedback\">Feedback</a></p>		\n										<img src=\"http://4retirees.com/wp-content/uploads/elementor/thumbs/Support4Retirees-nwagg5eism1odj408eme6w8dn2vsry4lbfxghepczk.png\" title=\"Support4Retirees\" alt=\"Support4Retirees\" />											\n		<p>If you have questions, we want to answer them. The following answers a number of frequently asked questions weve already identified. So have a read and if your question hasnt been answered here or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>		\n										<img width=\"528\" height=\"353\" src=\"http://4retirees.com/wp-content/uploads/Support4Retirees-Banner-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://4retirees.com/wp-content/uploads/Support4Retirees-Banner-1.jpg 528w, http://4retirees.com/wp-content/uploads/Support4Retirees-Banner-1-150x100.jpg 150w, http://4retirees.com/wp-content/uploads/Support4Retirees-Banner-1-300x201.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 528px) 100vw, 528px\" />											\n			<h2>Learn all about 4Retirees\n</h2>		\n												What is 4retirees?					\n					<p>4Retirees is a purpose-built community for retirees. Its a place where experience meets opportunity. 4Retirees was created with one clear focus; to help retirees easily take advantage of a new world of opportunities. Its a meeting place of ideas, inspiration, and experienced people. One of those opportunities is the online and on-demand economy that offers a new way to future-proof your retirement dreams. This new way of working lets you earn additional income while still maintaining the freedom to do the things you love most. No one knows better than a retiree how much the world can change in a lifetime. And 4Retirees is the network that helps you keep up with and benefit from those changesall at a pace youre comfortable with.</p>\n												Do I have to be tech-savvy to use 4Retirees?					\n					<p>No. 4Retirees is run for retirees, by retirees. Weve made it easy for you to get started. If you can read and tap on a keyboard, you can participate now and take our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>. And, when youre ready to learn some new technology skills, well be there too. Our aim is to help you to keep pace with this burgeoning economy and part of that is upskilling your technology skills. These improved skills will help you to unlock a future filled with more opportunities for earning income, taking advantage of tools available to you, so that you can live your dream retirement life and keep you better connected to your friends, family, and the rest of the world.</p>\n												Who participates in 4Retirees community?					\n					<p>Anyone who is chasing a dream of freedom is participating in the 4Retirees community. Anyone who is thinking of career change to enable their potential and opportunities can participate in our community and take advantage of whats on offer. If you have an interest in the on-demand economy, we invite you to start your journey here by taking our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check.</strong></a></p>\n												In what ways will I be able to connect with other retirees?  					\n					<p>Our vision is to build a better place for all retirees. Our big goal at first is to bring you all together and to establish the connections. We know that people do business and learn from people they know, like, and trust. So, first things first, well concentrate on providing opportunities to come together so we can all benefit the advantage of the technology and the on-demand economy. We want to create a community of retirees4retirees, eventually we can co-create, build a better place with a better economy where all retirees come to connect, interact, meet, help each other, share their skills, build new ones, volunteer, earn money, and maybe even make some friends! We will provide you soon with opportunities to participate in forums, to connect, chat, share ideas, and ask questions about your fellow community members. You can also connect with the community through most of our social media channels. Make sure to sign up for our eNewsletter so we keep you up to date on our progress as our community grows and becomes an even better place for retirees.</p>\n												How do I manage my subscription preferences?					\n					<p>Once you take our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> or sign up to our eNewsletter, we will create an account for you and send you link to activate via email. You can manage your preferences by accessing right top corner of your account under the button that says &#8216;<a href=\"http://4retirees.com/my-account\" data-wplink-url-error=\"true\">Login</a>&#8216; or <a href=\"http://4retirees.com/my-account\" data-wplink-url-error=\"true\">My account</a>. If you would like to receive our weekly eNewsletter with useful tips and hints, or perhaps you would like to update your interest information so that we can provide you with more comprehensive updates weekly, you can do all of that in through your account preferences.</p>\n												I forgot my password, how do I reset it?					\n					<p>You can manage this under your account &#8211; right top corner &#8211; you can request a password reset, or before you login, reset by clicking on <a href=\"http://4retirees.com/wp-login.php?action=lostpassword\" data-wplink-url-error=\"true\">forgot my password</a>.</p>\n												How do I deactivate my account? 					\n					<p>We would certainly be sorry to see you go, but if you really want to, you can simply unsubscribe from all the communication or you can deactivate your account. You can manage these preferences under the <a href=\"http://4retirees.com/my-account\" data-wplink-url-error=\"true\">My Account</a> tab located in the right top corner, through the button, Deactivate Account.</p>\n		<p>If we didn\'t answer your question or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>		\n			<h2>Learn all about on-demand economy</h2>		\n												What exactly is the on-demand economy?					\n					<p>The on-demand economy is defined as the economic activity created by technology companies that fulfil consumer demand via the immediate provisioning of goods and services. The on-demand economy, also known as a sharing economy or collaborative consumption or the peer economy, is a trending business concept that highlights the ability (and perhaps the preference) of individuals to rent or borrow goods or services and not necessarily buy and own them. Owners rent out something they are not using, such as a car, house, bicycle, or their skills, to someone else using these peer-to-peer services and earning money on demand.</p>\n												Can you give me some examples of businesses in the on-demand economy? 					\n					<p>We have a comprehensive list of over hundreds of on-demand economy businesses right here in Australia. Two that you have most likely heard of are UBER and Airbnb. With UBER, people use their own cars, sign up as drivers, and then transport people or deliver food to other people as part of their peer-to-peer network. You can work on your terms, the hours you want, in the area you want, and still earn money while meeting new people and listening to your favourite radio station. The second example is Airbnb. It is an online marketplace and hospitality service for people to lease or rent short-term lodging including holiday cottages, rooms, apartments, homestays, hostel beds, etc. You can do this all year long if you have a place you never use, for weeks at a time when you are travelling, or just until you find new tenants for your investment property. Its a great contemporary (and cheaper) alternative to hotel accommodation. We can match you with hundreds of these types of businessesthe choice of businesses participating in the on-demand economy is virtually endless and new ones are popping up all the time. Youll be able to find transportation, hobby-related businesses, travel, education, business services, delivery, pet care, and the works!</p>\n												Why is the on-demand economy growing so fast?					\n					<p>The <strong>on-demand economy </strong>is here to stay. And its growth is a given. Whether its renting a room, hiring a driver, renting a parking space, or outsourcing household tasks, the sharing economy is disrupting a range of industries and causing regulators to take note. Technology is making it easier for new marketplaces to be created. Services that used to be high touch, slow to deliver, but yet expensive are now fast and efficient, thanks to technology like smart phones. This creates a better experience for the consumer and also the person providing the service. Australia has a supportive start-up community with new businesses starting up all the time, and we are here to provide you with this comprehensive research in discovering new options for earning an income all the time. Its an incredibly exciting time!</p>\n												How can I start earning money in the on-demand economy? 					\n					<p>The first step is to understand your compatibility with the opportunities available. Take our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> and see if your current circumstances match any of these on-demand businesses and how much you could potentially earn. Once you receive your results, then you decide if it makes sense for you to purchase access to your custom <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List </strong>so that you can then pursue your matching income-generating opportunities.</p>\n												How much I can get paid from the on-demand economy? 					\n					<p>Once you buy your personalised and comprehensive <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List</strong>, you can explore each individual opportunity you matched with, sign up to do it, start working, and start earning from your very first day. In the on-demand economy, you have the potential to earn per hour, per day, per week, or per item or project. Its possible to earn anywhere from $20 per hour to thousands of dollarsor moreper week or per month. Your earning potential depends on your skill set, situation, the opportunities available, and how little or how much youre prepared to do. The choice is yours! And, youre not locked into committing to any time frames. You can dip in or out when it makes sense for you.</p>\n												How do I get paid from these individual on-demand economy businesses?					\n					<p>Each of these businesses have their own individual payment systems and conditions that you should review before signing up. Payment is usually made directly to your bank account or PayPal account. Fast payment is one of the benefits of the on-demand economy. After you have provided a service via one of the on-demand economy businesses, some payments are received within 1-3 business days, others or on a designated day each week or month. We definitely recommend that you to check this with each business before you start. And, we recommend speaking with your accountant or tax/financial adviser about your individual circumstances.</p>\n												Is the on-demand economy legal?					\n					<p>The on-demand economy and participation in it is most definitely legal and it is even supported by Australian Government. You, as a participant in it, are fully supported by Australian Consumer Law while using the on-demand sharing economy. To find out more, <a href=\"http://consumerlaw.gov.au/business-and-the-acl/sharing-economy-platforms/\">CLICK HERE</a>.</p>\n												Do I pay TAX or/and GST when earning on-demand economy? 					\n					<p>The Australian Government is fully supportive of participation in the on-demand economy and has introduced a number of protection laws for consumers, including taxation and GST. In general, just like other sources of employment, the on-demand economy is subject to taxation and GST. The Australian Tax Office has some helpful information about tax and the on-demand economy GST, to find out more, <a href=\"https://www.ato.gov.au/general/the-sharing-economy-and-tax/income-tax-and-GST-in-the-sharing-economy/\">CLICK HERE</a>. If you need more information, we then recommend you to contact your accountant or tax/financial adviser to assess your personal circumstances.</p><p>If we didn&#8217;t answer your question or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>\n		<p>If we didn\'t answer your question or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>		\n			<h2>Learn all about the Free Income Compatibility Check</h2>		\n												What is the Free Compatibility Check?					\n					<p>Our compatibility check is designed to match your personal circumstances with the opportunities that are most relevant to you. We have designed a short 14-question checklist to better understand your current personal and economic situation, e.g. Do you own a car? Do you like helping others? Etc. This short <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> takes just a minute to complete and it can identify all sorts of opportunities for you.</p>\n												Why should I complete a Free Compatibility Check?					\n					<p>Your answers from the <strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong> are matched with over hundreds of available opportunities to earn income in the on-demand economy. Once youve completed it, we will send you an email with your personalised and comprehensive list containing on-demand economy businesses that match your responses and situation. The results will help you to understand both the number and dollar value associated with the available on-demand earning opportunities available to you through the 4Retirees community. We match people with opportunities and this mix changes all the time. We will update you as new businesses appear and/or if new questions are added to the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>. Results are processed automatically, in real time and personalised specifically for you, based on your answers to the survey questions.</p>\n												Who should take the Free Compatibility Check?					\n					<p>We believe that anyone who is the least bit interested in earning additional income should take part in the on-demand economy, and therefore should take our <strong><a href=\"#FICC\">Free Compatibility Check</a>.</strong> The on-demand economy is here to stay and is expected to represent the new world of work for generations to come. Why shouldnt you take advantage of these opportunities too? To participate in the on-demand economy you need to be at least 18 years old. We are the business that proudly supports retirees and their desire to stay relevant. We connect retirees with on-demand income opportunities as it can be difficult for you to identify these businesses with fast moving technologies and it may require advance research techniques that you just dont have access to. We want to make it simple for you. So, this <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> is available and open for you and almost anyone else in Australia who would like to earn on demand income. So feel free to recommend this <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> to your friends and family no matter of their age or status.</p>\n												How does the Free Compatibility Check work?					\n					<p>We have developed an online digital matching tool that asks you 14 short questions, and then utilises a rating and matching system to present you with opportunities suitable to your circumstance. We match you with available on-demand economy opportunities in real time. We believe we can provide you with a 98% match compatible with you. With your personalised <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>On-Demand Opportunities List </strong></a>you choose whats the most relevant and best fit for you at the current time. We intentionally dont promise a 100% match, as your individual circumstances can change daily and we might not be privileged to any of your personal information that might disqualify you from the participation e.g. the year of your vehicle, suspension of your driving license, etc.</p>\n												How much does the On-Demand Opportunities List cost?					\n					<p>To understand your opportunities and earnings potential, you can simply take our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>. Once you understand the number and scope of these earnings opportunities, you then make a decision if you would like to purchase the personalised and comprehensive <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List </strong>for a one-time cost of $149AUD. After your on time payment we will continue update you as new businesses appear and/or if new category questions are added to the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>, all of that will be done for you on an ongoing basis and for free.</p>\n												How do I decide whether or not to buy my personalised and comprehensive On-Demand Opportunities List?					\n					<p>This is certainly up to you. Its your personal decision to buy or not to buy this opportunity list. We want to create great experiences as well as opportunities. Only you are aware of your own wants, needs, and situation. We suggest using the common sense and good judgement that got you this far. Every situation is different. For instance, if the results only matches you with one or two opportunities of total possible earnings, $200, its probably not worth purchasing yet. However, if your results match you with 10 to 20 or more businesses and your total earning could be as much as $1,800 a month or upwards of $20,000 a year, then this could be a terrific investment as it represents a number of potentially profitable opportunities for you. </p>\n												What should I expect to get once I buy my personalised On-Demand Opportunities List? 					\n					<p>You will get a list of the individual businesses that your current personal circumstances have been matched with. The list can be as long as 100 businesses or more. It all depends on the answers you provided in our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> and the matching opportunities available. The list will contain business name, conditions of participation, terms of use, how to start, how much you can earn from each individual business and sometimes, we even have deals or special codes for you to quote when signing up with specific businesses. Each of these businesses have a helpful customer service team that will assist you in the sign up process and/or answer any questions you might have about getting started. The faster you sign up and work, the faster you can start earning.</p>\n												Do I need any professional qualifications for the participation in these on-demand jobs?					\n					<p>The quick answer is that you dont need to have them, but if you do, then this can help you take even more advantage on demand opportunities e.g if you are an accountant or writer or teacher etc. From what we have researched you dont need any high-level special qualifications or university degrees to participate in many current on-demand economy jobs. Once you get your personalised<strong> On-Demand Opportunities List</strong> we will provide you with information and links to each business terms of use and conditions to ensure you understand all requirements of each business individually. Each of these on-demand economy businesses operate individually and have their own process and list of qualifications youll need to supply before you start earning. We dont know what the future holdsit could have opportunities for on-demand doctors, and then, lets hope theyre required to have professional qualifications!</p>\n												Are there any special requirements to sign up with on-demand businesses?					\n					<p>Once you get your<strong> On-Demand Opportunities List</strong>, you will then be responsible for familiarising yourself with each business on your list, and their requirements. You are also responsible for everything between signing up and starting to earn. Each of these businesses operate individually and have a different sign-up process as well as requirements, documents, or information that you will have to provide. And each of these business have a helpful customer service team to assist you with the process and/or answer any questions you may have.</p>\n												How often should I take the Free Compatibility Check?					\n					<p>We believe you should take the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> once, and get a fully personalised and comprehensive <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List</strong>. We will monitor the changes in the on-demand economy in the background, looking to identify new opportunities regularly. If we make significant changes to the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a>and/or introduce more on-demand economy business opportunities, we will notify you about those changes via email and explain how to get access to them. You will continue to get access, through your account with 4Retirees, to any new opportunities that are a match, and you wont pay any more than the original cost. Its a one-time payment that continues to give you access to the latest information and options that are suitable for you.</p>\n												Who is responsible for signing up with these on-demand economy businesses?					\n					<p>Once you take the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> and then decide to buy your personalised <strong>On-Demand Opportunities List</strong>, you will be responsible for becoming familiar with your matched opportunities. You can pick and choose one at a time or simply try to sign up with all of them straight away yourself. Each of these businesses operate individually and have different sign up processes and requirements. They also have a helpful customer service team to assist you with sign up and/or any questions you might have. Its up to you to decide how many businesses and how quickly you want to sign up to start earning. You will also receive a number of helpful tips from us via email to assist you with starting to earn straightaway. But, there is no obligation. If you purchased your list and decide that you dont want to pursue any opportunities on it that is perfectly fine and completely up to you.</p>\n												Is this personalised and comprehensive On-Demand Opportunities List relevant to my friends or family, can I share with them?					\n					<p>The list is personalised to you and your current, personal circumstance. So, we strongly advise you not to share it with your friends and family as they might have very different circumstances and eligibility criteria. Neither you nor 4Retirees wants to be seen as potentially misleading them. We would highly recommend that you send our <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> to your friends and family to take it for themselves. Then they can check their own compatibility, see their own individual opportunities, and decide for themselves whether or not to take the next step.</p>\n												How much, as a retiree, can I earn in addition to my pension? 					\n					<p>The Australian Government has introduced taxation and conditions for retirees relating to the on-demand economy. Please visit this Government page and learn about your individual earnings strategies and also contact your accountant or tax/financial advisor to discuss further strategies to maximise your earning potential and understand the implications to your pension and taxes. To learn more from government <a href=\"https://www.ato.gov.au/general/the-sharing-economy-and-tax/income-tax-and-GST-in-the-sharing-economy/\">CLICK HERE</a>.</p>\n												Do I need to have an Australian Business Number (ABN) or any special types of insurance? 					\n					<p>Each on-demand economy business has their own requirements and sign up criteria. Some may require an ABN or insurance, but most of them will just require your Tax File number to track your earnings. We recommend you read the FAQs and the terms and conditions for each of the businesses you are considering working with before you start. If you are planning to share or rent out your home, car, or other valuable personal items, then you may find it helpful to discuss the situation with your insurer as well.</p>\n												What happens when some of the options I have matched with on my On-Demand Opportunities List arent servicing my particular area?					\n					<p>The on-demand economy is fast growing, so if the option that interests you isnt servicing your area yet, hopefully, it will soon. We recommend that you speak with the businesses of your particular interest and see if they have any plans to grow in your area, as most of them are continuing to expand. We do our best to give you different options for the same category in an attempt to minimise that problem for you, but we appreciate that it does exist. And, we continue to add additional on-demand businesses as fast as we can.</p>\n												The options that you have listed in my On-Demand Opportunities List are unfamiliar to me  what should I do?					\n					<p>Most on-demand economy businesses listed are small and medium-sized businesses. Brand awareness increase very gradually; It takes a long time for everyone to hear about such brands or discover their need for them. One of the advantages you have is that you are aware of these opportunities now, before they become mainstream. Take the <a href=\"#FICC\"><strong>Free Compatibility Check</strong></a> and see what is on the offer, and if it is a good fit for you, you may be one of the pioneers in a whole new business!</p>\n		<p>If we didn\'t answer your question or you need additional clarification, email us at <a href=\"mailto:faq@4retirees.com\">faq@4retirees.com</a> and we will respond to you just as quickly as we can!</p>		\n			<h2>Work With Us </h2>		\n		<p>If youre interested in a career that helps retired people make the most of their experience, youve come to the right place.</p><p>Were always on the lookout for talented, experienced and enthusiastic people like you. Its an opportunity to join our start up at an early stage and play a part in shaping its success.</p><p>We are offering both volunteer and paid work (part time and flexible arrangements, working remotely or from your home). Does this sound like a good opportunity for you? Contact us at <a href=\"mailto:career@4retirees.com\">career@4retirees.com</a></p>		\n			<h2>Feedback</h2>		\n		<p>4Retirees welcomes your suggestions, your feedback, including complaints. We believe people have a right to speak up, as it helps us to see what works for you, what doesn\'t, and where we can make improvements to provide you with a better opportunities and a better service. Your opinion matters, email us at <a href=\"mailto:feedback@4retirees.com\">feedback@4retirees.com</a></p>','Support Centre','','inherit','closed','closed','','56-revision-v1','','','2018-09-19 14:38:16','2018-09-19 05:08:16','',56,'http://4retirees.com/uncategorised/56-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(123,1,'2018-09-19 14:40:46','2018-09-19 05:10:46','{\"4retirees::ocean_header_top_padding\":{\"value\":\"30\",\"type\":\"theme_mod\",\"user_id\":1,\"date_modified_gmt\":\"2018-09-19 05:09:50\"},\"4retirees::ocean_header_right_padding\":{\"value\":\"20\",\"type\":\"theme_mod\",\"user_id\":1,\"date_modified_gmt\":\"2018-09-19 05:09:50\"},\"4retirees::ocean_header_bottom_padding\":{\"value\":\"25\",\"type\":\"theme_mod\",\"user_id\":1,\"date_modified_gmt\":\"2018-09-19 05:09:50\"},\"4retirees::ocean_header_left_padding\":{\"value\":\"30\",\"type\":\"theme_mod\",\"user_id\":1,\"date_modified_gmt\":\"2018-09-19 05:09:50\"},\"4retirees::ocean_header_mobile_top_padding\":{\"value\":\"5\",\"type\":\"theme_mod\",\"user_id\":1,\"date_modified_gmt\":\"2018-09-19 05:10:46\"},\"4retirees::ocean_header_mobile_right_padding\":{\"value\":\"10\",\"type\":\"theme_mod\",\"user_id\":1,\"date_modified_gmt\